fend, opening the way for the liberalization of immigration and citizenship policies. It is a thought-provoking analysis that sheds light on the dynamics of membership politics and policy making in contemporary liberal-democratic countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCitizenship -- Government policy -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aCitizenship -- Government policy -- Germany -- History -- 20th century. 0aCitizenshipxGovernment policyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aCitizenshipxGovernment policyzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aEmigration and immigration -- Government policy -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aEmigration and immigration -- Government policy -- Germany -- History -- 20th century. 0aEmigration and immigrationxGovernment policyzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEmigration and immigrationxGovernment policyzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aMulticulturalism -- Canada -- History -- 20th century. 0aMulticulturalism -- Germany -- History -- 20th century. 0aMulticulturalismzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMulticulturalismzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481568040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774815680423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774815680/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook